---
// Funder's Slate Audit Checklist — parallel to the Writers' Room Checklist.
// Static markup, printable. Intended to be used while reviewing a slate of
// films / commissioned content before greenlight, mid-development reviews,
// or annual portfolio reviews.
---
<div class="panel p-6 md:p-10 print:bg-white print:text-black">
  <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-gold-400">Funder's Slate Audit Checklist</p>
  <h3 class="mt-1 font-display text-2xl text-white">
    10 questions to ask of a slate before you commit.
  </h3>
  <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-white/60 max-w-2xl">
    Funding decisions usually evaluate plot, talent, market, and budget — but
    the gendered patterns the slate amplifies often get reviewed only after
    release, when changes are expensive. This checklist surfaces the
    norm-shaping decisions a slate is implicitly making, in the same window
    as the commercial decision. Use it during pipeline review, before
    greenlight, or as a portfolio audit.
  </p>

  <ol class="mt-8 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">01.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Across the slate, who tends to feel shame, and for what?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">02.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Who tends to feel pride, and what are they being celebrated for?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">03.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If we plotted the gendered weight of every project on this slate, what shape does the slate have overall?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">04.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Which projects amplify the dominant patterns of their region's cinema, and which complicate them?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">05.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">For projects that depict shame around victimhood (harassment, violence, abuse), how is the scene resolved — restitution, consequence, or silence?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">06.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Which themes appear in projects led by women writers, directors, producers — and which don't?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">07.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If audiences in the target market are shifting (per the Diverging Mirror), which projects on this slate are tracking the shift, and which are pulling against it?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">08.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Are there themes the slate is over-indexed on — to the point of crowding out other stories?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">09.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Where on this slate is there room — story, format, talent — to surface a counter-treatment of a dominant trope?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">10.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">A year from release, what would you want to be able to say this slate moved — and how will you know whether it did?</span>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 text-xs text-white/40">
    <button onclick="window.print()" class="rounded-full bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-white/70 ring-1 ring-white/10 hover:bg-white/10 hover:text-white transition print:hidden">
      Print this checklist
    </button>
    <span>or screenshot — it's CC-BY.</span>
  </div>
</div>
